Description: Vintage 1965 Hofner Senator Type 66 Cherry Sunburst Guitar 4.3lbsType 66 (cutaway) Senator in a lovely rare sunburst finish. Beautiful German goodness in exceptional condition. We have acquired this, along with a few other Hofners, from a guy who looked after all his guitars with great pride! This is in exceptional original condition - you really will struggle to find another better. The original sunburst finish has very little crazing, unlike most of this age, and has only a few small blemishes around the edges. We love what has happened to the back of the neck - the original finish is starting to fide to an orange colour. Beautiful! The neck is extremely sturdy and holds true. We cannot see anything that has been changed on this, including the tortoise shell pickguard. Weight: 4.3lbsSerial: 291Please have a close look at the high resolution photographs below, as these form part of our description.Please note, for all you musicians and collectors outside of Europe, this guitar will need a CITES certificate to accompany the export of this guitar, due to inclusion of the restricted rosewood material. This application process can only be started once purchased, costs £59 on top of the price of the guitar, and can add on up to 15 days to the posting off process. Please get in touch for more information before purchasing.At The Music Locker we will do all we can for you to get the instrument you want. You're more than welcome to come along and have a play on this through one of our vintage amplifiers!
